com.absynth.battleship.players

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.absynth.battleship.players.PlayerAdapter
      • com.absynth.battleship.players.User
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Player

    public class User
extends PlayerAdapter
    Represents a human Player of the BattleshipBoard game.
    Will query the user for each task and will expect a response in the given Scanner.

    NOTE: Will not close the scanner.
    Author:
    David Boivin (Absynth)

      • responseValidation

        private Coord responseValidation(java.lang.String response)
        Method used to confirm that the user response to a coordinate query is valid by checking:
        1. the length of the response (response.length == 2 )
        2. Checks if the coordinate created by the 2 character coordinate is valid
        Parameters:
        response - The user response to validate
        Returns:
        Will return a valid Coord or null if the response is invalid.
